Fire in the hole 🔥
Late season is here!

We couldn’t have drew this one up any better last night in Iowa. Our first sit of the late muzzleloader season on public land provided. The good Lord has truly blessed us this hunting season. We are very excited to share season 10 in the near future.

📸 @nadingbr
Thank you to everyone who came out to support us at the @iowadeerclassic this past weekend. This was our best show yet. We are excited to catch up with everyone again next year.
Picked up some 2022 head gear today

Yesterday was a memorable day in the Iowa timber. When my grandpa Leonard passed away many years ago, I was given his old Winchester model 12 shotgun. For years I said I wanted to honor him by shooting a turkey with that gun and yesterday turned out to be that day. It was a hunt I will never forget and I’m sure he is was proudly looking down to witness it all happen.

📸 @aaronskrzypczak

We made quick work the past couple days here in Iowa. After @nadingbr put me on birds the last couple years it was nice to finally return the favor. Now it’s time to head north to finish out the spring in the flats.
10th annual beatdown weekend didn’t disappoint. What a turkey season it has been. Now it’s time to start focusing on bucks.

Some Assembly Required. New @cageblinds up on the permission property this week. This spot should be 🔥 come November. Shout out to our interns @rossweeks22 and @charlie_cork for sticking it out with me in the Iowa heat.
Having a place to go is a home. Having someone to love is a family. Having both is a blessing from God.
We beat the heat last night in North Dakota. What an incredible start to the season. Our intern @charlie_cork killed it on the lens.

You just can’t beat nights that end like this.

📸 @charlie_cork

Happy 5 year anniversary on this special day to my best friend @mlmancl. Thank you for doing this walk through life with me and putting up with my crazy quirks each and every day. I love you so much and can’t wait for what the next 5 years have in store for us.

John 4:7

“Dear friends let us love one another, for love comes from God. Everyone who loves has been born of God and knows God.

Tuesday evening will be a hunt I will never forget. Since we moved to Iowa, one of my biggest goals has been to get @mlmancl on a nice buck. We hunted hard in 2022 but luck just wasn’t on our side. After a few sits this fall it all came together during the early muzzleloader season. This was our first successful deer hunt together on film. I’m so proud of Melissa’s patience and persistence over the past couple seasons. We are forever grateful for our good friend Brad for getting us access to hunt the farms we are on. We are also thankful for @rossweeks22 and @charlie_cork to give us a hand transporting and processing the deer.

Although my Wisconsin rut trip didn’t go as planned I was fortunate enough to wrap my antlerless tag on this unique piebald doe. What an incredible once in a lifetime opportunity to harvest a deer like this. Checkout the hunt on our YouTube channel.

📸 @charlie_cork

This Iowa season has been a grind for me but we were lucky enough to catch up to a solid public land buck last night. Huge shout out to @jimbofuego for sticking it out with me the last week. The 3-5 mile hikes a day were hell but what a memory it made.
